{"name": "nipcat", "metadata": {"name": "nipcat", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["click", "rich", "netifaces"], "summary": "ip calculator", "upload_time": 1732776882}, "documentation": ["<div align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"./logo.png\" alt=\"nipcat Logo\" width=\"200\">\n  <h1>NipCat</h1>\n  <p>TCP/IP Swiss Army Knife</p>\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/walidsa3d/actions/workflows/test.yml\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/walidsa3d/nipcat/test.yml?branch=main&style=flat-square\" alt=\"Test Status\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/walidsa3d/nipcat/blob/main/LICENSE\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/license/walidsa3d/nipcat?style=flat-square\" alt=\"License\">\n  </a>\n</div>\n\nNipCat is a TCP/IP Swiss Army Knife.\n\n## \ud83d\ude80 Features\n\n\n## Installation\n```\npip install nipcat\n```\n\n## Usage\n```\nnipcat -i\nnipcat 192.168.0.1/22\n```\n\n## \ud83e\uddd1\u200d\ud83d\udcbb Contributing\n\nContributions are welcome! Please feel free to submit a Pull Request.\n\n## \ud83d\udcc4 License\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License. See the LICENSE file for more details.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "nipcat.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo.get_external_ip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Retrieves the external IP address using multiple fallback services.\n\nAttempts to get the external IP address using various public IP API\nservices. If one service fails, it automatically tries the next one.\n\nReturns:\n    str: The external IP address if successful.\n    None: If unable to retrieve the external IP address.\n\nNote:\n    The method tries multiple services in case some are unavailable:\n    - api.ipify.org\n    - api.ipapi.com\n    - api.myip.com"]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo.is_physical_interface", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "iface", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Checks if a network interface is physical.\n\nUses multiple methods to detect physical interfaces:\n1. Checks for virtual interface naming patterns\n2. Examines sysfs path for physical device presence\n3. Verifies interface driver information\n\nArgs:\n    iface (str): Name of the network interface\n\nReturns:\n    bool: True if interface is physical, False otherwise"]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo.get_interfaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "NetworkInterface", "xref": {"fqname": "nipcat.types.NetworkInterface", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Retrieves information about all network interfaces.\n\nGathers detailed information about each network interface including\nIP addresses, MAC addresses, netmasks, and broadcast addresses.\n\nReturns:\n    List[NetworkInterface]: A list of NetworkInterface objects containing\n        information about each network interface.\n\nNote:\n    - Skips the loopback interface ('lo')\n    - Only includes interfaces with IPv4 addresses\n    - Handles errors for individual interfaces gracefully"]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetworkInfo.get_hostname", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Retrieves the system hostname.\n\nReturns:\n    str: The hostname of the system."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Class providing methods to gather network information.\n\nThis class contains static methods for retrieving various network-related\ninformation including external IP, internal network interfaces, and system\nhostname."]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetCalc", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "nipcat.utils.NetCalc.is_ipv4", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ip", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Validate IP address format."]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetCalc.is_private_ip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ip", "type": {"name": "IPv4Address", "xref": {"fqname": "ipaddress.IPv4Address", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check if IP address is private."]}, {"name": "nipcat.utils.NetCalc.is_valid_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mask", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["_summary_\n\nAr